<% content_for(:title, "Chris — Christopher Quentin McMullen-Laird") %>

<!-- Biography -->
<section class="max-w-3xl mx-auto mb-16">
  <h1 class="text-4xl font-title text-stone-800 mb-2">Christopher Quentin McMullen-Laird</h1>
  <p class="text-lg text-blue-800 mb-8">Conductor &middot; 1984&ndash;2020</p>

  <div class="space-y-4 text-stone-600 leading-relaxed">
    <p>
      American conductor Christopher Quentin McMullen-Laird will start the 2019-2020 season in his new
      post of Music Director of the Jaeren Symfoniorkester in Norway. He started his career at the
      Bayerische Staatsoper in Munich, where he prompted over 50 opera productions, working alongside
      Music Directors Kent Nagano and Kirill Petrenko.
    </p>
    <p>
      Christopher has conducted productions for Cape Cod Opera, Opera Providence, Opera Rogaland,
      Schlosstheater Rheinsberg, Tokyo Opera Association, and the education department at the Bayerische
      Staatsoper. He has also assisted on dance productions at the Royal Ballet and Rambert Dance
      Company in London.
    </p>
    <p>
      In addition to his work in opera and ballet, Christopher enjoys a busy and varied concert schedule.
      He was previously Music Director of the Munich International Orchestra, the Bjergsted
      Symfoniorkester and the Phoenix Youth Orchestra, and has appeared as guest conductor with the
      Dartington Festival Orchestra, the Filharmonia Zielenogorska, and the Abaco Orchester.
    </p>
    <p>
      Christopher has extensive experience working with amateurs and young musicians as a regular
      workshop assistant for BBC Learning and the Royal College of Music Sparks programmes.
      Christopher was a Leverhulme Arts Scholar at the Royal College of Music London where he earned
      a Master&rsquo;s of Music in Conducting.
    </p>
    <p>
      At the RCM he performed with all major ensembles and developed a particular interest in
      memorisation and performing music with movement. Christopher&rsquo;s work in these fields won him
      the 2018/2019 Mercers&rsquo; Arts Award for combining theoretical knowledge with public performance.
      He earned his Bachelor&rsquo;s degree at Dartmouth College in New Hampshire, USA, and has held
      Fellowships at the Hochschule f&uuml;r Musik Weimar and the University of Stavanger.
    </p>
  </div>

  <!-- Repertoire -->
  <details class="mt-8">
    <summary class="text-blue-800 font-medium cursor-pointer">View full repertoire</summary>
    <div class="mt-4 space-y-6">
      <div>
        <h3 class="text-lg font-title text-stone-700 mb-2">Operas Conducted in Performance</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-1 text-stone-600 text-sm">
          <li>Cherubini &mdash; <em>Le porteur d&rsquo;eau</em> (world premiere of new critical edition 2008)</li>
          <li>Gershwin &mdash; <em>Blue Monday/135th Street Blues</em> (Jazz Opera)</li>
          <li>Griffeath-Loeb, B. &mdash; <em>Sicut erat</em> (world premiere 2004)</li>
          <li>Hamlisch &mdash; <em>A Chorus Line</em></li>
          <li>Humperdinck &mdash; <em>H&auml;nsel und Gretel</em> (in German, excerpts)</li>
          <li>Ishita, E. &mdash; <em>The Town in the Sky</em></li>
          <li>Jenkins, K. &mdash; <em>Eloise, an opera for young people</em></li>
          <li>Kleiberg, S. &mdash; <em>David and Bathsheba</em> (first fully-staged production 2015)</li>
          <li>Leh&aacute;r &mdash; <em>The Merry Widow</em> (in English)</li>
          <li>Mozart &mdash; <em>Bastien und Bastienne</em>, <em>La clemenza di Tito</em> (excerpts), <em>Le nozze di Figaro</em> (excerpts)</li>
          <li>Purcell &mdash; <em>The Tempest</em></li>
          <li>Sibata &mdash; <em>Forgotten Boys</em> (German premiere 2011)</li>
          <li>Weber &mdash; <em>Abu Hassan</em></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3 class="text-lg font-title text-stone-700 mb-2">Operas Assisted &amp; Prompted</h3>
        <p class="text-stone-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">
          Works by: Beethoven, Bellini, Berlioz, Bernstein, Britten, Bizet, Donizetti, Dvor&aacute;k, Handel,
          Henze, Humperdinck, Jan&aacute;&#269;ek, Lloyd-Weber, Mayr, Messiaen, Mozart, Mussorgsky, Poulenc,
          Puccini, Ravel, Rossini, Srnka, Strauss (J. and R.), Tchaikovsky, Verdi, Wagner, Weber,
          Widmann, and Zemlinsky.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </details>
</section>

<!-- Gallery -->
<% if @gallery_photos.any? %>
  <section class="mb-16">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-title text-stone-700 text-center mb-8">Gallery</h2>
    <div class="grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-4 gap-4 max-w-6xl mx-auto">
      <% @gallery_photos.each do |photo| %>
        <div class="aspect-square overflow-hidden rounded-lg">
          <%= image_tag photo.photo, class: "w-full h-full object-cover" if photo.photo.attached? %>
        </div>
      <% end %>
    </div>
    <div class="text-center mt-4">
      <%= link_to "Submit Photos", new_photo_submission_path, class: "text-blue-800 hover:text-blue-700 text-sm" %>
    </div>
  </section>
<% end %>

<!-- Add a Memory CTA -->
<section class="bg-stone-100 rounded-lg p-8 text-center mb-16 max-w-3xl mx-auto">
  <h2 class="text-2xl font-title text-stone-800 mb-3">Share a Memory</h2>
  <p class="text-stone-600 mb-6">
    Did Chris touch your life? Add your story, photo, or moment to the timeline.
  </p>
  <% if user_signed_in? %>
    <%= link_to "Add a Memory", new_memory_path, class: "inline-block px-6 py-3 bg-blue-800 text-white rounded hover:bg-blue-700 transition font-medium" %>
  <% else %>
    <%= link_to "Sign in to Add a Memory", new_user_session_path, class: "inline-block px-6 py-3 bg-blue-800 text-white rounded hover:bg-blue-700 transition font-medium" %>
  <% end %>
  <p class="text-stone-400 text-sm mt-3">
    or <%= link_to "share a tribute", new_tribute_path, class: "text-blue-800 hover:text-blue-700 underline" %> without an account
  </p>
</section>

<!-- Timeline -->
<section class="max-w-3xl mx-auto mb-16">
  <h2 class="text-2xl font-title text-stone-700 mb-8">Timeline</h2>
  <% if @memories.any? %>
    <div class="border-l-2 border-blue-300 ml-4 space-y-8">
      <% @memories.each do |memory| %>
        <div id="memory-<%= memory.id %>" class="relative ml-8 scroll-mt-20">
          <div class="absolute top-1 -left-[2.6rem] w-4 h-4 rounded-full bg-blue-600 border-2 border-white"></div>
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-800 font-medium"><%= memory.date.strftime("%B %d, %Y") %></p>
          <% if memory.title.present? %>
            <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-stone-800"><%= memory.title %></h3>
          <% end %>
          <% if memory.content.present? %>
            <p class="text-stone-600 mt-1"><%= truncate(memory.content, length: 300) %></p>
          <% end %>
          <% if memory.photos.attached? %>
            <div class="flex gap-2 mt-2">
              <% memory.photos.limit(3).each do |photo| %>
                <%= image_tag photo.variant(resize_to_limit: [200, 200]), class: "rounded" %>
              <% end %>
            </div>
          <% end %>
        </div>
      <% end %>
    </div>
    <div class="text-center mt-8">
      <%= link_to "View Full Timeline →", memories_path, class: "text-blue-800 hover:text-blue-700 font-medium" %>
    </div>
  <% else %>
    <p class="text-stone-400 italic text-center">No memories yet. Be the first to share one.</p>
  <% end %>
</section>

<!-- Tributes -->
<section class="max-w-3xl mx-auto mb-8">
  <h2 class="text-2xl font-title text-stone-700 mb-4">Tributes</h2>
  <p class="text-stone-500 mb-8">Kind words from people whose lives he touched.</p>
  <% if @tributes.any? %>
    <div class="space-y-6">
      <% @tributes.limit(10).each do |tribute| %>
        <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg shadow-sm border border-stone-200">
          <p class="text-stone-600 leading-relaxed mb-3"><%= truncate(tribute.content, length: 300) %></p>
          <p class="text-blue-900 font-medium text-sm">&mdash; <%= tribute.name %></p>
        </div>
      <% end %>
    </div>
    <div class="text-center mt-8">
      <%= link_to "Read All #{@tributes.count} Tributes →", tributes_path, class: "text-blue-800 hover:text-blue-700 font-medium" %>
    </div>
  <% end %>
</section>
